# Frontend – React conventions

- Use React Router for navigation; keep route components in `src/pages/*`.
- Data fetching via TanStack Query; keep API calls in `src/api/*` (create when needed).
- **Forms (required):** Every form must have validation — no raw submit handlers without schema validation. Use **React Hook Form** with **`zodResolver`**. Define Zod schemas in **`@autohub/shared`** when the same rules apply on the backend (preferred); otherwise colocate a schema next to the page or under `src/` as a small module. Wire user-facing error strings through **i18n** (`en` + `uk`), not hardcoded in the schema on the client (pass `t('…')` into schema factories where the project already does so).
- UI: Tailwind + shadcn/ui; shadcn components live in `src/components/ui/*`.
- Use `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` for className merging.
- All user-facing text must be added via i18n (e.g. react-i18next) with at least `en` and `uk` translations; do not hardcode strings directly in JSX/TSX.

